definition.value: Involved in catalyzing the release of a nascent polypeptide chain from a ribosome.
Catalysis of the reaction -  peptidyl-proline (omega-eq-180) -eq- peptidyl-proline (omega-eq-0).
Catalysis of the rearrangement of both intrachain and interchain disulfide bonds in proteins.
Catalysis of movement along a polymeric molecule such as a microfilament or microtubule, coupled to the hydrolysis of a nucleoside triphosphate.
Catalysis of movement along a microtubule, coupled to the hydrolysis of a nucleoside triphosphate (usually ATP).
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with monomeric or multimeric forms of actin, including actin filaments.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with monomeric actin, also known as G-actin.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an actin filament along its length.

Catalysis of the hydrolysis of the beta-(1--gt-4) linkages between N-acetylmuramic acid and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues in a peptidoglycan and between N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues in chitodextrins.

Catalysis of the reaction -  protein glutamine + alkylamine -eq- protein N5-alkylglutamine + NH3. This reaction is the formation of the N6-(L-isoglutamyl)-L-lysine isopeptide, resulting in cross-linking polypeptide chains -  the gamma-carboxamide groups of peptidyl-glutamine residues act as acyl donors, and the 6-amino-groups of peptidyl-lysine residues act as acceptors, to give intra- and intermolecular N6-(5-glutamyl)lysine cross-links.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an antigen, any substance which is capable of inducing a specific immune response and of reacting with the products of that response, the specific antibody or specifically sensitized T-lymphocytes, or both. Binding may counteract the biological activity of the antigen.

Catalysis of a biochemical reaction at physiological temperatures. In biologically catalyzed reactions, the reactants are known as substrates, and the catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein, but RNA that has catalytic activity (ribozyme) is often also regarded as enzymatic.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + D-glucose-6-phosphate -eq- UDP + alpha,alpha-trehalose-6-phosphate.
Catalysis of an oxidation-reduction (redox) reaction involving an alpha-ketoacid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-(alpha-D-mannosyl)-beta-D-mannosyl-R + UDP-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine -eq- 3-(2-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl]-alpha-D-mannosyl)-beta-D-mannosyl-R + H(+) + UDP.

Catalysis of the reaction -  CMP-N-acetylneuraminate + alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2--gt-3)-beta-D-galactosyl-R -eq- CMP + alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2--gt-8)-alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2--gt-3)-beta-D-galactosyl-R.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + beta-D-galactosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl-R -eq- UDP + beta-D-galactosyl-(1--gt-3)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1--gt-6)]-N-acetyl-D-galactosaminyl-R.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-glucosamine + beta-D-mannosyl-R -eq- UDP + 4-(N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl)-beta-D-mannosyl-R.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-galactose + N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminylglycopeptide -eq- UDP + beta-D-galactosyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminylglycopeptide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-beta-alanyl dopamine + H2O -eq- dopamine + beta-alanine.
Catalysis of the synthesis of beta-alanyl-dopamine from the precursor dopamine (3,4-dihydroxyphenylethylamine).
Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-carotene + O(2) -eq- 2 retinal.

Catalysis of the reaction -  CMP-N-acetylneuraminate + beta-D-galactosyl-(1--gt-4)-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine -eq- CMP + alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2--gt-6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1--gt-4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  CMP-N-acetylneuraminate + beta-D-galactosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-R -eq- CMP + alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-(2--gt-3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1--gt-3)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-R.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-carbamoyl-beta-alanine + H2O -eq- beta-alanine + CO2 + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + 5-alpha-cholest-8,24-dien-3-beta-ol -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 24-methylene-5-alpha-cholest-8-en-3-beta-ol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (5-L-glutamyl)-L-amino acid -eq- 5-oxoproline + L-amino acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (5-L-glutamyl)-peptide + an amino acid -eq- peptide + 5-L-glutamyl-amino acid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + 1-acyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate -eq- CoA + 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycerol-3-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate + NAD+ + H2O -eq- L-glutamate + NADH + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + [(1--gt-3)-beta-D-glucosyl](n) -eq- UDP + [(1--gt-3)-beta-D-glucosyl](n+1).
Catalysis of the transfer of a segment of a (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-glucan chain to a primary hydroxyl group in a similar glucan chain.
Catalysis of the reaction -  an 11-beta-hydroxysteroid + NAD(P)+ -eq- an 11-oxosteroid + NAD(P)H + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + 2-acylglycerol -eq- CoA + diacylglycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-acetyl-1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + H2O -eq- 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine + acetate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-amino-4-hydroxy-6-hydroxymethyl-7,8-dihydropteridine + ATP -eq- (2-amino-4-hydroxy-7,8-dihydropteridin-6-yl)methyl diphosphate + AMP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-erythrose 4-phosphate + H(2)O + phosphoenolpyruvate -eq- 7-phospho-2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-arabino-heptonate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-deoxy-D-glucose-6-phosphate + H2O -eq- 2-deoxy-D-glucose + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-galactose + 2-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphingosine -eq- UDP + 1-(beta-D-galactosyl)-2-(2-hydroxyacyl)sphingosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-methyl-2-oxobutanoate + acetyl-CoA + H(2)O -eq- (2S)-2-isopropylmalate + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-methylbutanoyl-CoA + acceptor -eq- 2-methylbut-2-enoyl-CoA + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a 3-beta-hydroxy-delta(5)-steroid + NAD+ -eq- a 3-oxo-delta(5)-steroid + NADH + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-dehydroquinate -eq- 3-dehydroshikimate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  7-phospho-2-dehydro-3-deoxy-D-arabino-heptonate -eq- 3-dehydroquinate + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA + NAD+ -eq- 3-oxoacyl-CoA + NADH + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-3-hydroxybutanoate + NAD(+) -eq- acetoacetate + H(+) + NADH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-3-hydroxybutanoyl-CoA -eq- crotonoyl-CoA + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-hydroxy-2-methylpropanoyl-CoA + H2O -eq- CoA + 3-hydroxy-2-methylpropanoate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-isopropylmalate -eq- 2-isopropylmaleate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-carboxy-2-hydroxy-4-methylpentanoate + NAD+ -eq- 3-carboxy-4-methyl-2-oxopentanoate + NADH + H+.
